{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772547227,"nonce":"0XwmoGkL/OAqN38kAlpWnNCMJXU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vbSoh","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/332","origin":"github"},"title":"Refactor Makefile with stamp-file dependencies and consolidate scripts","message":"## Context\n\nFollow-up to #325 (ADR: Makefile vs just). Once the ADR is accepted, implement its recommendation: refactor the Makefile to use stamp-file dependencies so that `make build` works correctly from a fresh clone and skips already-completed steps on subsequent runs.\n\nPart of #263 (Simplify scripts and Makefile interface).\n\n## Problem\n\nThe current Makefile has 19+ targets that are all independent — no dependency graph. A fresh-clone workflow requires the user to know and run `make bootstrap`, `make setup-all`, and `make build` in the correct order. Re-running setup when nothing changed wastes time.\n\n## Requirements\n\nFrom [#325 discussion](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/325#issuecomment-3984784129):\n\n1. **Stamp-file dependency graph** — use `.make/*.done` stamp files so Make tracks which steps have completed\n2. **`make build` from fresh clone** — automatically runs bootstrap → manifest → layer setups → build\n3. **Incremental re-runs** — skip already-completed steps; re-run layer setup only when its `.repos` file changes\n4. **`make test` depends on `make build`** — setup is handled transitively\n5. **Preserve `make help`** — self-documenting targets continue to work\n6. **Preserve `generate-skills`** — slash command generation unaffected\n7. **Stamp invalidation** — decide on strategy (simple touch vs hash-based) for detecting when scripts themselves change\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Depends on #325 (ADR accepted first)\n- Must not break existing `generate-skills` / slash command pattern\n- `.make/` directory should be gitignored\n- Consider worktree interaction (`.make/` is workspace-global, shared across worktrees)\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Should bootstrap stamp be invalidated when `bootstrap.sh` changes? (hash-based stamp)\n- Should a manifest symlink guard verify the symlink exists before trusting its stamp?\n- Any targets that should *not* participate in the dependency graph?\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}